SUMMARY:The Silliad: Improvised Myths and Legends
LOCATION:London
DESCRIPTION:Why do geese fly south for the winter? What's really inside an 
 Oreo? You suggest the question\, then watch it be answered through myth\, m
 ayhem and madness! From the roaring thunder of Mount Olympus to the frozen 
 tundra of Scandinavia\, it's Horrible Histories meets Clash of the Titans m
 eets Whose Line Is It Anyway? If you love improv\, this is not a show to my
 th! The Silliad return to the Camden Fringe after a debut in 2024 described
  as " quippy\, light-hearted\, and most importantly\, fun" by NW Londoner. 
 Mythology just got a whole lot sillier! Watch the audience become the myth-
 makers as they decide which pantheon is performed on stage by our skilful b
 ards. Whether it be Greek\, Norse or Egyptian\, The Silliad will answer the
  audience's deepest questions. "One of the most hilarious and sweet shows a
  person can watch." ★★★★★ (The Student) "Improv at its finest ...
  Not to be missed!" ★★★★★ (EdFringe Review) "Bringing something w
 holly unique to the stage" ★★★★ (Theatre & Tonic) "Mind melting" 
 ★\nMore info: https://comedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/the-silliad-impr
 ovised-myths-and-legends/
